<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1058,1198,1279]" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[562,694,1198,1219]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">sparicapillus</emphasis>
, is a Latin compound name that stems from 
<emphasis box="[274,351,1228,1249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">sparsus</emphasis>
(= few) and 
<emphasis box="[488,568,1227,1248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">capillus</emphasis>
(= hair); with reference to the patches of white setae on the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
